OL,3,CAristocrat and partner told off for
OL,4,C'disrupting' sentencing over baby death
OL,6,FIt was argued on behalf of both
OL,7,Fdefendants that the judge should
OL,8,Freject the prosecution case that baby
OL,9,FVictoria died of hypothermia and
OL,10,Faccept she was accidentally smothered,
OL,11,Fas they claimed.
OL,13,FPreviously, the court had heard how
OL,14,Fthe defendants exposed Victoria to
OL,15,Fdangerous conditions when they went
OL,16,Finto hiding to avoid her being taken
OL,17,Finto care, as four other siblings had
OL,18,Fbeen before.
